  "prompt": "What do boxers say to each other when in the ring?",
  "response": "In the boxing ring, boxers typically communicate in various ways:\n\n1. Verbal exchanges\n- Trash talk or taunting\n- Encouragement or challenges\n- Occasional motivational words\n\n2. Non-verbal communication\n- Gestures\n- Body language\n- Facial expressions\n\n3. During corner breaks\n- Coaches give strategic advice\n- Boxers receive instructions and encouragement\n\n4. Some common phrases might include:\n- \"Come on!\"\n- \"Let's go!\"\n- Insults or provocative statements\n- Short, intense motivational remarks\n\n5. Professional boxers often try to maintain focus and might not talk much during the actual fight, preferring to concentrate on their strategy and opponent's movements.\n\nThe specific content of communication varies widely depending on the individual boxers, their personalities, and the intensity of the match.",
